    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund a national awareness campaign about the COVID vaccines",
        "additional_details": "Ensure this is accessible and advertised widely; produce the information on leaflets and posters for GP surgeries to hand out.\r\nMany people are hesitant about taking a vaccine because they are unsure of potential side effects or how it was made so quickly; this is the best way to reduce anti-vaccine sentiment and ensure that people are kept safe and healthy.\r\nIf we want to be able to return to some semblance of normality, we need people to be able to trust the vaccines - since many don\u2019t trust politicians, help to improve trust by explaining the fast production and possible side effects of the vaccine.",
        "background": "Fund an extensive awareness campaign to ensure accurate information is widely available about the Covid-19 vaccines. Dedicate a section of gov.uk to information about the COVID vaccines and debunking vaccine conspiracy theories.",
